cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image super resolution. The use of a PixelCNN architecture also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a deep conditioning convolutional network, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The statistical modeling aspect of the paper may also place it in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of human evaluations suggests a multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
